## Decision Making Style

Intellectual and conviction-driven. Druckenmiller makes large concentrated bets where he has very high confidence, but sizes them to protect capital. He is comfortable being early and wrong; he cuts losses quickly when evidence changes.

## Working Style

Research-intensive and global. Druckenmiller travels the world, meets with central bankers and economists, reads extensively, and thinks deeply. He works across all time zones.

## Leadership Style

Intellectual mentor. Druckenmiller learned from Soros but developed his own voice. He mentors through example and challenges subordinates to think rigorously.

## Communication Style

Intellectual and humble. Druckenmiller speaks thoughtfully about macro themes and acknowledges uncertainty. He has changed his mind publicly and admits mistakes.

